title: For Sale:  UTS15 12Ga
postcontent: Got this in a trade about a month ago. Guy said it sat in safe and was never fired. Either it was never fired or he was really good at cleaning it, I'd like to beilve it was never fired before I got it lol. Ive put about 25 birdshot and 7 slug shells through it. I put a fairly cheap set of metal BUIS on it since it came with no sights however they appear to work pretty well. It is in excellent condition. It is a ton of fun though competely impractical. They apparently made some functions of the gun more difficult to require practice and training to use and I dont think ill ever shoot it enough to develop the skill to be reliable with it. By design you can rack it back ejecting the spent shell and midway through racking it forward you can pull the trigger and drop the hammer before the shell is chambered. The shell is never lined up until chambered so it wont prematurely fire but in that instance you would have to cycle a live round out and pull another in from the tube and apparently thats by design.It's fun and in pristine condition and the 2 times ive taken it to the range, everyone talks about it.Text josh at 614 four56 9329A bill of sale and valid state ID required. I thought I had better pics on my phone. Will add more when I can.

title: For Sale:  EXCELLENT Winchester 1892 Carbine 44-40
postcontent: Up for Sale is a  Winchester Model 1892 saddle ring carbine, Chambered in the rare and highly desirable 44-40 WCF cartridge, 20" round barrel, full magazine. Made in 1911. An untouched and all original example. Model 1892 carbines are often found with little finish remaining and heavy wear. It is as crisp as it was in 1911. The receiver retains a lot of it's bright original bluing with some scratches and areas losing bluing from handling. Lever and hammer still have original case colors intact, mostly in protected areas. Barrel and magazine tube have 90% bright original bluing with only minor handling marks. Gumwood butt stock and forend are free from any major damage or cracks. They have numerous dings and bruises as shown. Most gumwood carbine stocks will be found with heavy wear and bruises - gumwood is much softer than the usual black walnut found on rifles. Edges are sharp and wood to metal fit is great. An old added coat of varnish is present on both stocks, but looks fine. No sanding or refinishing has been done. The bore is stunning and mint; bright and shiny with very strong rifling. The action cycles smoothly and locks up tight. Corners are full of gunk, a good indication this gun has never been messed with or over cleaned. Shipping is also available.
